705054f-a.title: Brooklyn: Humboldt Street - Herbert Street
705054f-a.text:
(1)
492-508 Humboldt Street, east side, between Herbert and Richard-
son Streets, showing a view of "Colonnade Now". (The land on which
these homes are located, belonged to William Conselyea in 1869).
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Cellection.
(2)
The sawe, as seen from the opposite direction and showing, in
the background, the station-house of Precinct 51 A of the Pelice Dept.
September 1928.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
705054f-a.folder: Humboldt Street & Herbert Street, Brooklyn, NY
